cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.CV

The paper presents a novel Reinforcement Learning algorithm for learning behavior in continuous action, state, and goal spaces, which is a common problem in robotics. Therefore, cs.RO (Robotics) is a highly likely sub-category. The algorithm uses non-parametric estimators to approximate optimal value functions, which is a common technique in machine learning and falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel sample augmentation technique to improve generalization in the goal space, which is related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The proposed algorithm is benchmarked using simulation and a real-world voltage controlled robot, which falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. Finally, the paper also mentions using computer vision techniques to extract features from the robot's camera, which is related to cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-category.
